The paper focuses on autonomous robotic grasping, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method uses a convolutional neural network for vision-based grasping detection (cs.CV) and visual manipulation relationship reasoning (cs.AI). The use of deep learning techniques also suggests a possible fit for the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the integration of vision and manipulation in a single system suggests a possible fit for the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
